    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Banská Štiavnica Town Council (Vienna, 22 January
                    1549)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">The Queen’s councillors have complained that due to the
                            urging of the opposite side, they have been experiencing abuses during
                            the lawsuit between Wolfgang Haller and the heirs of Peter Hillepradt in
                            terms of the summons, laws, and deadlines, and because the people of
                            Banská Štiavnica want to get through the lawsuit more quickly, they may
                            cause quite a big damage to Haller and the Queen. So, in order to avoid
                            even the perception of impropriety, no matter how much the other party
                            is urging them, they should not hurry, and they should observe the laws
                            and deadlines and make sure that Haller’s lawyer has at least one month
                            to inform the procurator, whom Haller and the Queen will appoint to
                            manage the affairs of the mining town.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Prudentes et Circumspecti Amici Honorandi! </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Consiliarii <persName>reginalis maiestatis</persName> hic
                        <placeName>Viennae</placeName> constituti conquesti sunt apud nos, quod ad
                    instantiam adversae partis in causa inter magnificum dominum
                        <persName>Wolffgangum Haller</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.1"
                        >Wolfgang Haller.</note> etc., et matrem ac assertos haeredes quondam domini
                        <persName>Petri Hilleprant</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.2"
                        >Peter Hilleprandt was a Deputy Count of the Chamber <hi rend="italic"
                            >(Unterkammergraf)</hi> in Banská Štiavnica during the 1530s, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Meier–Piiarinen–Wegera</hi> 2009, 13.</note> vertente
                    nimis inordinato processu, citatione, legitimis et debitis terminis, ac
                    dilationibus ad deliberandum, et respondendum non distincta, nec legitimae
                    praesentata nimis celeriter festinare velletis, ex quo non mediocre damnum in
                    dominum <persName>Haller</persName> ac praecipue <persName>reginalem
                        maiestatem</persName> redundare posset, de quo etiam legitime querelae ad
                        <persName>regiam maiestatem</persName> pervenire possent. Ita quod in non
                    levem suspicionem trahi possetis, quae cuilibet iudici maxime cavenda est,
                    adhortamur itaque nos amice admonendo, quod causam tanti ponderis et momenti
                    aliqua festinatione ac inordinatu processu, quantumvis instet adversarius, non
                    acceleretis, sed debitis et legitimis terminis ac iuridicis dilationibus hoc
                    negotium ita temperetis, ut advocatus domini
                        <persName>Haller</persName><placeName>Viennae</placeName> existens ad
                    minimum unius mensis spatium habere possit ad informandum
                        <persName>procuratorem</persName>, quem dominus <persName>Haller</persName>
                    et fortasse deinceps reginalis maiestas pro negotii qualitate ad civitates
                    montanas destinabit. Valete. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Ex <placeName>Vienna</placeName> vigesima secunda Ianuarii anno
                    Domini 1549. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">
                    <seg type="signature">
                        <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Nicolaus Olahus episcopus Zagrabiensis
                            et Agriensis cancellarius regius etc. manu propria</add>
                    </seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Prudentibus et circumspectis iudici et iuratis ceterisque civibus
                    Semnitiensis dominis et amicis nobis honorandis.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
